Cone-Rod Dystrophy is a rare genetic eye disorder that affects the cone and rod cells in the retina, leading to progressive vision loss. The global Cone-Rod Dystrophy market is expected to witness significant growth from 2021 to 2028. The market is segmented by type, diagnosis, treatment, and end-users. The key segments in the Cone-Rod Dystrophy market include autosomal dominant cone-rod dystrophy, autosomal recessive cone-rod dystrophy, and others. In terms of diagnosis, the market is bifurcated into genetic testing, electroretinogram, and others. The treatment segment includes medication, surgery, and other options. Furthermore, the end-users in this market comprise hospitals, specialty clinics, and others.

